social_posts.post_text:
1 WEEK AWAY FROM MY CHRISTMAS RECITAL IN GIBRALTAR!

Looking forward to this wonderful opportunity to sing my favorite Christmas music. If you happen to be in Spain, please join us in Gibraltar at the Cathedral of the Holy Trinity Church on December 15th at 8:00 p.m. for a wonderful program including works by: BIZET, PUCCINI, GOMEZ, BACH and more.

Thank you @gib_philharmonic for hosting this special concert. Also greatly looking forward to working with Philip Scriven, organist.

Happy holidays to everyone! 🎄🌟🇪🇸

AND HERE IT IS! THE NEWS IS OUT! 

I am delighted to announce my @metopera debut(s) for the 2023/24 season. 

I have the honor of performing two Puccini masterpiece operas -- La Rondine & Madama Butterfly, both of which will be broadcast live in HD 📡📺

It's always been a great dream of mine to sing at this historic opera house and to finally have the opportunity to share my voice with my hometown family and friends. I'm looking forward to seeing you all there for these incredible productions alongside a fantastic cast and the great @metorchestra & @metoperachorus ! 
See you next year! 🌟
#vivapuccini

'Amor ti vieta'

As we approach our final performance of Fedora I wanted to share the famous aria from Act II with all of you far and near. 

It has been a wonderful experience performing in this beautiful theater alongside a wonderful cast, orchestra and creative team. And for me, it was a true pleasure to bring the music of Giordano's Fedora to the Canary Islands for the very 1st time. A time I will always treasure for the future.

Thank you all and looking forward to returning very soon! Muchas gracias y hasta luego!

Toitoitoi 🌟🌟🌟

Amor ti vieta di non amar.
La man tua lieve, che mi respinge,
Cerca la stretta della mia man
La tua pupilla esprime: "l'amo"
Se il labbro dice: "non t'amerò"

Love forbids you not to love.
Your soft hand which pushes me away
seeks the firm gasp of my hand:
the pupil of your eye expresses "I love you"
if your lips say "I will not love you".

Lauded for his „vocally magnificent, radiant and distinctive tenor” voice (Opera Aktuell), Jonathan Tetelman has rapidly risen to become a major star of his generation.

Having had the great pleasure to meet the charismatic tenor for an inspiring interview about his recent roles as much as his forthcoming second album „The great Puccini“ which is due to be released by end of September 2023, I also learnt about the tenor´s most unforgettable experience on stage.

For me it soon becomes crystal clear, why opera is not only a gateway to the human soul, but first and foremost the tenor´s world.

Come and enjoy this very inspiring interview @operaversum_magazine, catch up on the insights given on the making of Jonathan Tetelman‘s new album and why music clips also play an important role in it.

📷Bernd Wolf

Mehr Adventstimmung, mehr Wien und mehr Besinnlichkeit geht nicht, wenn #Wirsymphoniker zum großen Adventkonzert laden. Dieses Jahr am 7. Dezember im spektakulären Ambiente des Wiener Stephansdoms.

Unsere erste Gastdirigentin Marie Jacquot @mcajacquot leitet durch ein vorweihnachtliches Programm mit besonderen Melodien - von Praetorius‘ „Es ist ein Ros entsprungen“ über Webbers „Pie Jesu“ hin zu Leopold Mozarts „Schneeflockenwalzer“, Tschaikowskis „Nussknacker“ und Malottes „Cantique de Noël“! Auf dem Programm stehen auch die großen Weihnachts-Klassiker wie Bachs „Jesus bleibet meine Freude“, das „Ave Maria“ von Gomez und – zum gemeinsamen Abschluss „O du fröhliche“. 

Mit uns singen die Sopranistin @fatmasaid.sop , der Tenor @tenortetelman und der @wienersingverein . Tickets für die Vorpremiere um 18:00 Uhr und das Konzert um 20:30 Uhr sind bereits erhältlich: LINK IN BIO!

Das traditionelle Adventkonzert der Wiener Symphoniker wird auch heuer in @orfdrei übertragen.

🎞️ @sohot.burningforart 
🎥 @orfdrei

O, Nature, full of grace,
Queen of time and space,
deign to welcome whoever passes
and salutes you, humble mortel.

Mysterious silence!... O solemn calm!
Everything attracts me and pleases me!...
This wall and this dark corner...
This limpid spring & coolness of the shade;
there’s not a hedge, there’s not a bush,
Where a flower doesn’t burst forth,
Where a shiver doesn’t pass by!

Oh, Nature, intoxicate me with your perfumes!
Mother, eternally young, adorable and pure,
Intoxicate me with your perfumes!
And you, sun, come and drown me in your crimson rays!
